summary: This is an email chain from April-May 2021 regarding technical issues with the production of discovery materials (SDNY_PROD011) in the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The correspondence involves discussions between parties (likely prosecutors and defense counsel) about difficulties defense counsel is having matching Bates numbers to metadata in a spreadsheet provided by the FBI.

events.title: Defense counsel reports difficulty with discovery metadata
events.description: Defense counsel expresses difficulty reviewing metadata on images in production 11, specifically in matching Bates numbered images to rows in an FBI-created spreadsheet.

events.title: Vendor provides overlay file for production
events.description: A vendor provides an overlay file containing production number, file name, and MD5 Hash for the SDNY_PROD011 Maxwell production to help resolve metadata matching issues.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain discussing technical issues with discovery production (SDNY_PROD011) in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
Defense counsel reported difficulty matching Bates numbered images to metadata rows in an FBI-created spreadsheet.
A vendor provided an overlay file to help resolve the metadata matching problem.
The correspondence shows ongoing logistical coordination between parties in the Maxwell case regarding discovery materials in April-May 2021.
